title: "John Chioles - Twilights Embrace"
date: 2024-12-30 12:00:00 -0000
author: John Chioles
quote: "As daylight fades to twilight,"
subject: Post-War Nature Poetry (Post-1930)
permalink: /Post-War Nature Poetry (Post-1930)/John Chioles/John Chioles - Twilights Embrace
---

As daylight fades to twilight,
the horizon wears a gown of gold,
each breath of wind carries whispers,
tales from the day long gone.

The stars begin their dance,
a melody of light and shadow,
a celestial celebration,
a promise of night to behold.

- John Chioles
